50|$|In 2004, a {{jury found}} that Nellcor infringed several Masimo patents related to measure-through motion and low {{perfusion}} signal processing technology. In 2005, {{the appellate court}} affirmed the infringement findings against Nellcor and instructed the District Court to enter a permanent injunction against Nellcor’s <b>pulse</b> <b>oximeters</b> (e.g., N-395, N-595) that were found to infringe. In January 2006, Masimo and Nellcor entered into a settlement agreement, where Nellcor, among other things, agreed to discontinue shipment of the <b>pulse</b> <b>oximeters</b> that were found to infringe Masimo’s patents.|$|R
