50|$|There are no {{reported}} {{adverse effects}} {{associated with this}} kind of treatment. However, symptoms of over-training may appear as a result of abusing basic training protocols supplied by manufacturers. Products that do not offer effective and instant monitoring and control over the treatment sessions must be avoided. <b>Pulse</b> <b>oximeters</b> should be used to monitor the level of arterial oxygensaturation that is the basic measure of hypoxic training dosage. Good brands have <b>pulse</b> <b>oximeters</b> integrated into the system and the best hypoxicators are equipped with automated biofeedback hypoxic training control mechanisms.|$|R
